Manchester City manager, Pep Guardiola, has revealed his side’s Champions League game plan against Atletico Madrid. Man City will on Tuesday night host Atletico Madrid in a Champions League quarter-final first-leg tie at Etihad Stadium. Speaking at his pre-match press conference, Guardiola said Man City would not give Atletico Madrid space, adding that they would put a lot of pressure on the LaLiga holders. The former Bayern Munich and Barcelona coach said, “Bernardo [Silva] says we have a plan, but we still haven’t spoken about the plan. “He knows me and he knows I have a plan in my mind. “In this competition, I learned that a plan is important. Don’t give space, don’t give an inch. Defend when you need to defend, attack when you can do it. “We need courage and intelligent decisions and that belongs to the players. I put a lot of pressure on them for these games. “They are the guys who have to win or lose the game so go out there and try to do it. They have done it many times and hopefully, tomorrow we can perform wel